---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageBanner from "../components/PageBanner.astro";
import SplitSection from "../components/SplitSection.astro";
import SectionHeader from "../components/SectionHeader.astro";
import CtaBand from "../components/CtaBand.astro";

import bannerImg from "../assets/photos/farm-entrance-fall.jpg";
import jennImg from "../assets/photos/jenn-riding-hero.jpg";
import breeImg from "../assets/photos/bree-riding.jpg";
import loparoFarm from "../assets/photos/lepore-farm-view.jpg";
import tonka from "../assets/photos/tonka.jpg";
import babyCat from "../assets/photos/baby-cat.jpg";
import doubleRainbow from "../assets/photos/double-rainbow.jpg";

const credentials = [
  "USDF Bronze Medalist",
  "USDF Silver Medalist",
  "Competed through Prix St. Georges",
];

const crew = [
  {
    name: "Tonka",
    role: "Chief of Security",
    img: tonka,
    alt: "Tonka, Jenn's English bulldog, lying contentedly in a pile of hay",
    body:
      "Jenn's bulldog Tonka supervises the barn aisle most days and takes her greeting duties very seriously.",
    position: "center 40%",
  },
  {
    name: "Baby Cat",
    role: "Barn Cat in Chief",
    img: babyCat,
    alt: "Baby Cat, the fluffy light-grey resident barn cat, on the barn mats",
    body:
      "Of the two resident barn cats, Baby Cat (light grey and endlessly photogenic) has a way of winning everyone over.",
    position: "center 35%",
  },
];

const description =
  "Meet Avastar Dressage: trainer and USDF bronze and silver medalist Jenn Czechowski, barn manager Bree Dolbec, the barn crew, and a genuinely supportive boarding community at Lepore Farm in Lincoln, Rhode Island.";
---

<Layout title="About" description={description}>
  <PageBanner
    image={bannerImg}
    alt="A stone pillar with a lantern and white fence at the entrance to Lepore Farm on an autumn evening"
    eyebrow="Our story"
    title="About Avastar"
    lede="A close-knit dressage barn where classical training and genuinely individualized care come standard."
    position="center 55%"
  />

  <!-- Jenn -->
  <SplitSection
    id="jenn"
    image={jennImg}
    alt="Jenn Czechowski riding a chestnut horse in an extended trot, in a navy show coat"
    eyebrow="Trainer & Owner"
    title="Jennifer Czechowski"
    imageSide="left"
    bg="oat"
    aspect="aspect-[4/3]"
    position="center 30%"
  >
    <p>
      Jenn built Avastar Dressage on classical principles, the same foundation
      that runs through her own riding and everything she teaches. As an
      instructor she's calm, patient, and quietly ambitious for her students:
      many have moved up the levels, earned USDF recognition, and been coached
      by Jenn at championship competitions.
    </p>
    <p>
      A USDF bronze and silver medalist, Jenn has competed through Prix St.
      Georges on clients' horses. These days her focus is on helping her
      riders chase their goals. She trains with Roel Theunissen and has ridden
      in clinics with Ann Guptill, Rita Brown, Lynn Kimball-Davis, Karl
      Mikolka, Sandy Osborn, Claudia Tarlov, and Robert Zandvoort.
    </p>
    <p>
      Before going out on her own, Jenn spent years as assistant trainer and
      barn manager for Delante Dressage, owned by Lou Denizard. In 2008 she
      founded Avastar Dressage, naming it for her first dressage partner
      Avastar, known around the barn as Harry.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-2.5">
      {
        credentials.map((c) => (
          <span class="rounded-full border border-brass/35 bg-brass-deep/8 px-3.5 py-1.5 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-brass-deep">
            {c}
          </span>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </SplitSection>

  <!-- Bree -->
  <SplitSection
    image={breeImg}
    alt="Bree Dolbec riding a dappled grey horse in a pink top under a blue sky"
    eyebrow="Barn Manager"
    title="Briana Dolbec"
    imageSide="right"
    bg="cream"
    position="center 25%"
  >
    <p>
      Bree has managed the barn at Avastar for five years, and she's a big part
      of why the horses look and feel as good as they do.
    </p>
    <p>
      Between Jenn, Bree, and their barn team, every horse gets noticed, every
      single day. It's that steady, hands-on attention that boarders notice
      first and come to count on.
    </p>
  </SplitSection>

  <!-- Welcoming committee -->
  <section class="bg-oat">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-20 md:py-24">
      <SectionHeader
        eyebrow="The welcoming committee"
        title="The four-legged (and short-legged) crew"
        intro="No tour of Avastar is complete without a proper introduction to the barn's unofficial staff."
      />
      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {
          crew.map((m) => (
            <article class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-line bg-cream shadow-sm">
              <div class="aspect-[4/3] overflow-hidden">
                <Image
                  src={m.img}
                  alt={m.alt}
                  width={880}
                  class="h-full w-full object-cover"
                  style={`object-position: ${m.position};`}
                />
              </div>
              <div class="p-7">
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-navy">{m.name}</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-brass-deep">
                  {m.role}
                </p>
                <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-ink/80">{m.body}</p>
              </div>
            </article>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lepore Farm -->
  <SplitSection
    image={loparoFarm}
    alt="A distant view of the white barn and indoor arena at Lepore Farm across a green field"
    eyebrow="The setting"
    title="Lepore Farm"
    imageSide="left"
    bg="cream"
    aspect="aspect-[4/3]"
    position="center"
    imgWidth={720}
  >
    <p>
      Avastar is based at Lepore Farm, a classic New England equestrian property
      on Angell Road in Lincoln, Rhode Island, just minutes from Providence and
      an easy drive from southeastern Massachusetts.
    </p>
    <p>
      It's the kind of place that feels a world away, but is closer than you'd
      think. Come see it for yourself.
    </p>
  </SplitSection>

  <!-- The community -->
  <SplitSection
    image={doubleRainbow}
    alt="A double rainbow over the outdoor arena and the patio seating at Lepore Farm"
    eyebrow="The community"
    title="Good people, cheering each other on"
    imageSide="right"
    bg="oat"
    position="center 60%"
  >
    <p>
      Horse sport comes with real ups and downs. Progress arrives in waves,
      setbacks sting, and it's easy to get discouraged along the way. What
      carries you through is the people around you, and that's where Avastar
      shines. This is a barn where everyone genuinely cheers for everyone else.
    </p>
    <p>
      You'll find every kind of rider here, at every level of experience,
      working toward all kinds of goals. What you won't find is anyone looking
      down on where somebody else is in the journey.
    </p>
    <p>
      It shows in the little things. Boarders linger after rides just to hang
      out. Summer brings barn parties and cookouts, and when someone has a win
      worth celebrating, in the saddle or in life, the whole barn turns out
      for it.
    </p>
    <p>
      A down-to-earth, encouraging atmosphere in a place this beautiful, with
      care and training this good, is hard to come by in the horse world.
    </p>
  </SplitSection>

  <CtaBand
    eyebrow="Meet us"
    heading="We'd love to show you around"
    body="The best way to get to know Avastar and the whole crew is to visit. Call Jenn to find a good time to stop by."
  />
</Layout>
